			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	<br />
	Essential Job Functions<br />
	Production&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	&bull; Manages departmental priorities as determined by the Plant Manager<br />
	&bull; Balances productivity, safety and morale while ensuring&nbsp; production of scheduled parts<br />
	&bull; Maintains proper inventory levels as defined by shipping and production schedules<br />
	&bull; Notifies Plant Manager if the schedule is not going to be completed and of any necessary changes<br />
	&bull; Trains new employees on process and procedures<br />
	&bull; Supervise daily operation of production of product and production employees<br />
	&bull; Confirms that standard operating procedures are being followed<br />
	&bull; Updates standard operating procedures as needed<br />
	&bull; Conducts continuous PDCA patrol to audit factory for: safety, quality, efficiency, scrap and 5S<br />
	&bull; Establishes daily tracking and reporting for manufacturing results</p>
<p>
	<br />
	The Production Supervisor is responsible for overseeing the day to day functions, processes and operation of the Production Floor to ensure 100% on time delivery, customer satisfaction, compliance with ISO 14001 and TS 16949, with a commitment to continuous improvement.</p>
<p>
	Employee Relations</p>
<p>
	&bull; Coaches and counsels employees according to the Employee Handbook and to ensure consistency in disciplinary actions<br />
	&bull; Performs evaluations and assist in departmental workforce planning and development<br />
	&bull; Participates in the interviewing and recommendation of Production Employees<br />
	&bull; Makes recommendations for training needs and position/personnel changes<br />
	&bull; Completes New Hire Training Documentation and submits to HR in timely manner<br />
	&bull; Evaluates and tracks employee skills and development</p>
<p>
	ISO 14001 and TS 16949 Responsibilities&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	&bull; Ensures employees are trained on and follow Standardized Work Procedures as defined by the ISO and TS Manuals<br />
	&bull; Participates in Continuous Improvement Activities<br />
	&bull; Contributes to internal and external system audits as needed</p>
<p>
	Safety and Environmental&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	<br />
	&bull; Accountable for recycling materials<br />
	&bull; Participates in safety inspections, meetings and training sessions</p>
<p>
	Tracking and Reporting&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	<br />
	&bull; Follows production budgets<br />
	&bull; Tracks production metrics and reports to team members daily/monthly<br />
	&bull; Verifies employee work orders<br />
	&bull; Verifies employee timesheets and track employee overtime</p>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	EEO</p>
